                <h2 id="anonymization">4. Our Anonymization Process</h2>
                <p>
                    At the core of Clear Window is our commitment to anonymity. Here's exactly how we protect your identity while maintaining review authenticity:
                </p>

                <h3>Verification Phase (Temporary Data Processing)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Document Upload:</strong> You upload proof of address or tenancy documentation</li>
                    <li><strong>Automated Verification:</strong> Our system verifies the document authenticity and your connection to the property</li>
                    <li><strong>Human Review (if needed):</strong> Edge cases are reviewed by trained staff under strict confidentiality agreements</li>
                    <li><strong>Verification Complete:</strong> Your connection is confirmed</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Anonymization Phase (Immediate)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Identity Stripping:</strong> All personally identifiable information is removed from your review</li>
                    <li><strong>Document Deletion:</strong> Original verification documents are permanently deleted within 48 hours</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Hashing:</strong> IP addresses and device identifiers are hashed and separated from review content</li>
                    <li><strong>Pseudonymization:</strong> Reviews are linked to a pseudonymized identifier, not your real identity</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>What Remains Public</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your review content (no identifying information)</li>
                    <li>Your rating</li>
                    <li>Verification status ("Verified Reviewer")</li>
                    <li>General time period of review (e.g., "November 2025")</li>
                    <li>Property/service being reviewed</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>What We Can Never Recover</h3>
                <p>Once anonymization is complete, we cannot:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Link your review back to your real identity</li>
                    <li>Reveal your identity to property owners or landlords</li>
                    <li>Share your verification documents with anyone</li>
                    <li>Identify you from the review content alone</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <h4>Technical Implementation</h4>
                    <p>
                        Our anonymization process uses cryptographic hashing with unique salts, making it computationally infeasible to reverse-engineer identities from anonymized data. This is not obfuscation—it's permanent, irreversible anonymization.
                    </p>
                </div>

